164
00:11:25,740 --> 00:11:28,500
Inspector on duty, please accompany the Enforcers to the site immediately.

165
00:11:28,500 --> 00:11:31,790
And just when I was hoping today would be quiet...

166
00:11:31,790 --> 00:11:35,540
Well, our shift just ended, so... good luck.

167
00:11:35,540 --> 00:11:38,340
Would you like me to cover for Kougami?

168
00:11:38,340 --> 00:11:41,130
No, that won't be necessary.

169
00:11:41,130 --> 00:11:44,260
Let's get going, Ms. Inspector.

170
00:11:46,970 --> 00:11:47,600
What?!

171
00:11:58,440 --> 00:12:02,530
Drones have been watching the entrances to the mall since the warning was triggered.

172
00:12:03,280 --> 00:12:05,700
They haven't caught anyone yet.

173
00:12:06,370 --> 00:12:11,540
In other words, whoever's elevating the Area Stress level is still in the mall.

174
00:12:12,250 --> 00:12:14,540
Are we going to use Dominators?

175
00:12:14,540 --> 00:12:17,460
We'll have them delivered to us as a precaution.

176
00:12:17,460 --> 00:12:19,800
but we probably won't need them.

177
00:12:20,340 --> 00:12:22,260
Well then, shall we go?

178
00:12:36,230 --> 00:12:37,730
Do you feel uncomfortable?

179
00:12:37,730 --> 00:12:42,320
I thought your generation was used to playing with holo-suits on.

180
00:12:42,320 --> 00:12:45,280
It feels a bit weird with my whole body as an Avatar.

181
00:12:45,280 --> 00:12:47,530
It's okay, so let me see.

182
00:12:47,530 --> 00:12:49,200
Oh, stop it.

183
00:12:49,200 --> 00:12:50,240
Not a chance!

184
00:12:57,790 --> 00:12:59,460
Oh, there's our man.

185
00:12:59,460 --> 00:13:01,380
On the right, hiding behind the front column.

186
00:13:03,050 --> 00:13:05,970
But... How can you tell without even using a scanner?

187
00:13:05,970 --> 00:13:08,800
A beast can sniff out another beast's scent.

188
00:13:13,680 --> 00:13:18,480
Excuse me. Could we please measure your Psycho-Pass?

189
00:13:38,670 --> 00:13:41,300
Whoa... It's looking pretty cloudy.

190
00:13:41,300 --> 00:13:44,170
My assessment is that you require emergency therapy.

191
00:13:44,630 --> 00:13:46,300
Please come with me.

192
00:13:46,840 --> 00:13:48,430
What? Why?

193
00:13:48,890 --> 00:13:50,890
I haven't done anything yet...

194
00:13:53,850 --> 00:13:56,390
So you really can identify latent criminals?

195
00:13:56,810 --> 00:14:01,400
With experience, you'll intuitively know at first glance when someone's up to no good.

196
00:14:02,070 --> 00:14:03,980
Committing crimes, or cracking down on them...

197
00:14:04,740 --> 00:14:08,910
Either way, they're talents that deal with criminal behavior.

198
00:14:08,910 --> 00:14:13,410
That's why my Crime Coefficient is so high.

199
00:14:15,040 --> 00:14:19,750
Thanks to that, I'm now treated like a hunting dog who gets all the dirty work.

200
00:14:20,330 --> 00:14:21,630
In the end...

201
00:14:22,210 --> 00:14:24,340
I was pretty useless in there, wasn't I?

202
00:14:24,840 --> 00:14:27,420
No, you were quite helpful.

203
00:14:27,420 --> 00:14:31,300
Enforcers can't walk around outside without an accompanying Inspector.

204
00:14:31,300 --> 00:14:33,600
But that's...

205
00:14:33,600 --> 00:14:35,180
We talked about this, right?

206
00:14:38,890 --> 00:14:41,440
After you bring Enforcers to the site,

207
00:14:41,440 --> 00:14:47,190
all you need to do is keep an eye on them to make sure they don't slack off,

208
00:14:47,190 --> 00:14:49,360
That's all you need to do.

209
00:14:49,360 --> 00:14:52,990
In other words, you're telling me not to do anything, right?

210
00:15:04,590 --> 00:15:07,550
Can I join you, Ms. Inspector?

211
00:15:08,170 --> 00:15:08,920
Sure.

212
00:15:18,180 --> 00:15:19,810
I thought you were already off duty today.

213
00:15:21,020 --> 00:15:23,940
We Enforcers are prisoners, you know.

214
00:15:25,690 --> 00:15:29,780
Even when we're off duty, there's nowhere else we can go besides the CID floor and our quarters.

215
00:15:31,030 --> 00:15:32,820
Well, sorry about earlier.

216
00:15:32,820 --> 00:15:35,830
I got kinda carried away.

217
00:15:35,830 --> 00:15:39,540
As you can see, all the other women

218
00:15:35,830 --> 00:15:39,540
who work here are scary as hell, so...

219
00:15:39,540 --> 00:15:44,540
I'm just glad that a cute girl like you joined the CID, Akane.

220
00:15:44,540 --> 00:15:46,750
Oh, can I call you Akane?

221
00:15:47,460 --> 00:15:48,550
Yeah, sure.

222
00:15:49,720 --> 00:15:55,890
But hell, an Inspector with the Public Safety Bureau? Crazy place to work, right?

223
00:15:55,890 --> 00:15:56,850
Why here?

224
00:15:59,770 --> 00:16:02,270
Do you think I'm not suited for it?

225
00:16:02,900 --> 00:16:07,520
After what happened yesterday, anyone would probably think that way.

226
00:16:08,230 --> 00:16:10,900
Sibyl's Judgment of my job aptitude

227
00:16:10,900 --> 00:16:13,450
exceeded the Bureau's employment standards, so here I am.

228
00:16:13,950 --> 00:16:16,450
That's the thing I don't get.

229
00:16:16,450 --> 00:16:18,870
If you passed the Bureau's standards,

230
00:16:18,870 --> 00:16:22,710
you must've gotten a good ranking for other places too, right?

231
00:16:22,710 --> 00:16:25,000
Couldn't you have picked a different job?

232
00:16:25,000 --> 00:16:25,710
Yeah.

233
00:16:27,000 --> 00:16:32,550
I got an A ranking for all thirteen ministries and agencies, not to mention six companies.

234
00:16:32,550 --> 00:16:33,180
What?

235
00:16:33,180 --> 00:16:34,380
S-Seriously?

236
00:16:34,970 --> 00:16:37,050
Yeah. But...

237
00:16:37,050 --> 00:16:40,180
For all the other jobs, there were at least one or two people besides me

238
00:16:40,180 --> 00:16:42,350
who got the same ranking.

239
00:16:43,350 --> 00:16:46,770
I was the only one who got an A ranking for the Public Safety Bureau.

240
00:16:46,770 --> 00:16:51,110
There were more than 500 students and I was the only one.

241
00:16:51,530 --> 00:16:57,030
So I thought that there must have been something that only I could do at the Bureau.

242
00:16:57,370 --> 00:17:00,200
If I went there, I thought I could find my purpose in life...

243
00:17:01,120 --> 00:17:03,790
I thought I'd be able to find out why I was born here and now.

244
00:17:06,040 --> 00:17:09,000
Do you think I'm wrong?

245
00:17:09,000 --> 00:17:12,970
I don't know. What makes you think that someone like me would have any idea?

246
00:17:12,970 --> 00:17:15,010
You could become anything.

247
00:17:15,010 --> 00:17:17,970
You could choose any kind of life.

248
00:17:17,970 --> 00:17:19,810
You've even agonized over it, right?

249
00:17:20,220 --> 00:17:21,850
That's incredible.

250
00:17:21,850 --> 00:17:25,020
You're just like those people from the days before Sibyl was created.

251
00:17:25,020 --> 00:17:28,360
Nowadays, the Sibyl System reads your talent

252
00:17:28,360 --> 00:17:32,690
and tells you the way of living that will bring you the most happiness.

253
00:17:33,240 --> 00:17:34,820
And yet, you're talking about your purpose in life?

254
00:17:34,820 --> 00:17:36,570
The reason you were born?

255
00:17:36,570 --> 00:17:40,780
I never even imagined there were people who stressed over things like that!

256
00:17:41,490 --> 00:17:45,000
I was flagged in a Psycho-Pass test when I was five.

257
00:17:45,000 --> 00:17:46,790
I've been a latent criminal ever since.

258
00:17:47,500 --> 00:17:49,880
No possibility for rehabilitation through treatment.

259
00:17:49,880 --> 00:17:52,500
That's why I'm here now.

260
00:17:52,500 --> 00:17:54,760
And I'd much rather be one of the Bureau's hunting dogs

261
00:17:54,760 --> 00:17:59,260
and take on assassination jobs than spend the rest of my life in an isolation facility.

262
00:18:00,760 --> 00:18:03,220
That was the only choice I had.

263
00:18:03,600 --> 00:18:07,440
I wasn't planning to be mean to you or anything,

264
00:18:09,860 --> 00:18:13,900
but I changed my mind. So I'll ask you again.

265
00:18:14,860 --> 00:18:18,570
Why did you become an Inspector?

266
00:18:33,710 --> 00:18:35,550
I'm so sorry!

267
00:18:35,550 --> 00:18:39,010
You don't see many Inspectors who'd apologize to an Enforcer.

268
00:18:40,090 --> 00:18:41,550
I guess you're angry, right?

269
00:18:42,220 --> 00:18:44,600
That was your decision.

270
00:18:44,600 --> 00:18:46,220
I have no right to complain.

271
00:18:48,770 --> 00:18:51,310
Was my decision wrong?

272
00:18:52,060 --> 00:18:57,190
Did I just stand in everyone's way and put them in danger?

273
00:19:01,320 --> 00:19:03,910
I've been an Enforcer for a long time.

274
00:19:04,910 --> 00:19:11,540
The hunting dogs' behavior of following orders to take down prey with neither hesitation nor doubt

275
00:19:12,420 --> 00:19:14,500
is ingrained in my hands.

276
00:19:15,130 --> 00:19:17,210
I just followed that gun's orders,

277
00:19:17,210 --> 00:19:19,470
and shot many latent criminals.

278
00:19:19,880 --> 00:19:22,510
It was for the good of society, I told myself.

279
00:19:22,510 --> 00:19:25,310
It was easier to just accept that logic without question,

280
00:19:25,310 --> 00:19:27,720
and past a certain point I didn't even think about it anymore.

281
00:19:28,520 --> 00:19:33,190
I didn't even think to look back at myself and what I was doing.

282
00:19:34,480 --> 00:19:36,190
I was a fool.

283
00:19:36,190 --> 00:19:39,150
Being a detective isn't about bringing people down.

284
00:19:39,150 --> 00:19:42,570
It's supposed to be about protecting people.

285
00:19:43,200 --> 00:19:44,830
Kougami...

286
00:19:44,830 --> 00:19:48,700
You decided what was right on your own.

287
00:19:48,700 --> 00:19:51,040
You were able to put justice before your duty.

288
00:19:53,500 --> 00:19:58,960
With a boss like you, I might be able to work as a detective, not just a dog.

289
00:20:04,180 --> 00:20:06,640
Thank you very much!

290
00:20:06,640 --> 00:20:09,640
You also don't see many Inspectors who'd bow to an Enforcer.

291
00:20:11,600 --> 00:20:14,600
If you had time to think about it with a level head,

292
00:20:14,600 --> 00:20:18,530
you would've tried not to shoot her, right?

293
00:20:19,400 --> 00:20:21,280
I don't know.

294
00:20:21,280 --> 00:20:23,570
I didn't hesitate at the time.

295
00:20:23,570 --> 00:20:25,530
I thought I'd die if I hesitated.

296
00:20:26,410 --> 00:20:28,030
I thought, "I don't want to die in a place like this.

297
00:20:29,080 --> 00:20:32,040
I cannot die here, no matter what!"

298
00:20:32,960 --> 00:20:34,920
That one thought consumed me.

299
00:20:36,130 --> 00:20:38,130
I have unfinished business to take care of.

300
00:20:38,500 --> 00:20:41,590
There's something I have to settle no matter what!

301
00:20:42,550 --> 00:20:43,550
Kougami!

302
00:20:56,350 --> 00:21:00,530
So, you're saying that you made the right decision at the time?

303
00:21:00,940 --> 00:21:04,240
Is that your conclusion, Inspector Tsunemori?

304
00:21:04,650 --> 00:21:08,910
Yes. Her Crime Coefficient was only temporarily elevated.

305
00:21:09,240 --> 00:21:12,870
In fact, the therapy she's receiving after being taken into custody is going well,

306
00:21:12,870 --> 00:21:15,370
and her Psycho-Pass is recovering.

307
00:21:15,960 --> 00:21:18,290
Kougami, is there anything you want to say?

308
00:21:19,290 --> 00:21:23,010
No. Inspector Tsunemori fulfilled her duty.

309
00:21:23,550 --> 00:21:24,510
That is all.

310
00:21:40,520 --> 00:21:46,450
It seems all fairy tales are dead

311
00:21:45,700 --> 00:21:50,450
It seems all fairy tales are dead

312
00:21:51,200 --> 00:21:55,790
In a hospital ward of brick stones

313
00:21:56,670 --> 00:22:00,880
my voice is too coarse to sing

314
00:22:01,880 --> 00:22:06,010
Outside in the foggy haze

315
00:22:07,220 --> 00:22:11,600
a red moon glows

316
00:22:12,560 --> 00:22:16,980
Look at me

317
00:22:17,810 --> 00:22:22,520
Do not avert your gaze

318
00:22:23,900 --> 00:22:26,820
Behind black bars

319
00:22:26,650 --> 00:22:29,530
I was born

320
00:22:29,320 --> 00:22:31,950
I wish there were a punishment for evil

321
00:22:31,740 --> 00:22:34,830
Always I need you

322
00:22:34,620 --> 00:22:37,500
Now, grant us justice

323
00:22:37,290 --> 00:22:40,000
before chaos takes us all

324
00:22:39,830 --> 00:22:44,300
Pay the price of fate and let us go together,

325
00:22:43,960 --> 00:22:50,050
nameless beasts

326
